# .env.local.example
#
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in real values.
# .env.local is NOT committed to git (it is in .gitignore).
# This example file IS committed so future developers know what variables exist.
#
# HOW TO USE:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.local.example .env.local
# 2. Fill in any values that apply to your environment
# 3. Restart the dev server after changes

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MARKER: ISBN SERVICE PROVIDER
# V1 uses direct HTTP calls to Syndetics / Open Library / Google Books.
# No API keys are required for V1 — all sources used here support unauthenticated
# access at library-scale volume.
#
# FUTURE: When the AI-enhanced wrapper is built, the ISBN service will be
# replaced by an MCP connector (Supabase Edge Function). If that connector
# requires an API key or JWT, add it here.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Syndetics client ID — embedded in cover image URLs.
# Default for SCL is "sunflowerco" (already hardcoded in isbnService.ts).
# Only override here if the client ID changes.
# SYNDETICS_CLIENT_ID=sunflowerco

# Google Books API key — optional. Basic ISBN lookups work without a key,
# but a key raises rate limits. Leave blank for V1.
# GOOGLE_BOOKS_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MARKER: FUTURE AUTH CONFIG
# V1 has no authentication. If auth is added later, credentials/secrets
# would be added here (e.g., NextAuth secret, OAuth client IDs).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NEXTAUTH_SECRET=
# NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000
